Combine canola oil, beer, honey, mustard and pepper in a sealable plastic bag. Remove 2 tablespoons of marinade; set aside. Add pork to remaining marinade and squeeze bag to coat pork with marinade; seal bag. Let stand 30 minutes in the refrigerator. Remove chops from marinade and pat dry; discard marinade. Grill chops over low heat for 30 minutes or until done, basting occasionally with reserved marinade.